Attorneys General Urge U.S. Senate to Confirm Consumer Nominee

-- B y   C a r t e r   D o u g h e r t y
-- 
2011-10-18T14:57:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/attorneys-general-urge-u-s-senate-to-confirm-consumer-nominee.html
A group of 37 state and territorial
attorneys general today urged the U.S. Senate to confirm  Richard
Cordray  as the first director of the Consumer Financial
Protection Bureau, according to a letter released by the
 National Association of Attorneys General .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carter Dougherty in Washington at 
 cdougherty6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lawrence Roberts at 
 lroberts13@bloomberg.net  